;------------------Amer's Office---------------
;May 1997
;
NUMBER 1410
NAME Amer's Bottle
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
REGION 203
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are in a large circular room with walls of a green opaque glassy material
that lets soft green light filter in. Multicolored silk hangings cover much
of the walls. The roof of the room arches high above you the in the center of
the room, soars up forming what looks like a chimney with a tiny dark opening
barely visible. The center of the room is dominated by a bed made of a pile
of pillows, rugs and quilts under a silken canopy supported by two golden
columns. Around the perimeter of the room are benches covered in colorful
silks, offering places for visitors to rest.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;-------------------- dump lost folks --------------------------
IFLOGIN
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER Welcome home.
    ECHO OTHERS %N smiles as %s arrives in %h home.
  ELSE
    MOVEGROUP 201
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;-------------------my bed-------------------------------
ITEM 0 84 ADJ1=163 ADJ2=63
EXTEND 0 made of a pile of soft woolen rugs, quilts and silk pillows
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The huge bed looks comfortable.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;------------------------opening-------------------------------------
ITEM 2 72 VAL2=205
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
High up in the center of the ceiling is a tiny opening.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;----------------------benches-------------------
ITEM 6 339 ADJ1=63
;-------------------------verbs-------------------
IFPREVERB SMELL -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The scent of exotic spices fill the room.
  ECHO OTHERS %N smiles as %s breathes deeply.
ENDIF
;-----------------------------sit------------------------
IFPREVERB SIT -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You sit onto a bench.
    ECHO OTHERS %N smiles as %s leans back on a silk covered bench.
    POSITION SIT
ENDIF
;----------------------------lay-------------------------------
IFPREVERB LAY -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You recline onto a comfortable bench.
    ECHO OTHERS %N seems very relaxed as %s reclines on a silk covered bench.
    POSITION LAY
ENDIF
;-----------------------------get in bed------------------------
IFPREVERB GO 0
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You sit in the bed and a beautiful dijinna appears from the bedding and begins to massage your shoulders.
    ECHO OTHERS %N sits on the bed and a beautiful dijinna appears from the bedding and begins to massage %h shoulders.
    POSITION SIT
  ELSE
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You start to sit on the bed when a scantily dressed dijinna appears from the bedding and begins to scream.
    ECHO OTHERS %N starts to sit on the bed and a beautiful dijinna appears from the bedding, looks at %N and starts to scream.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;----------------------------go opening-------------------------------
IFPREVERB GO 2
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You feel yourself dispersing into a cloud and are blown out of the bottle.
  ECHO OTHERS %P dissolves into a cloud of smoke and flows up toward the opening.
  AFFECT ITEMVAL2
  ECHO ALL %P appears in a cloud of smoke.
  AFFECT 1410
  MOVEGROUP ITEMVAL2
ENDIF
;-----------------------------------------------
;----------------Fall  Across 1998 ----------------
;-----------Declare variables for timers-----------
VARIABLE COMMFERRY
VARIABLE COMMDOCK
VARIABLE ACROSSMIN
;--------Variables used for random echoes---------
VARIABLE ACROSSPLAZA
VARIABLE CARAVANCOURT
VARIABLE HOUNDSTEETH
VARIABLE DOCKSEVENTS
VARIABLE HRPLAZA
VARIABLE RIVEREVENTS
;--------Variables used for wagon movement-------
; current location, X,Y go from 0,0 to 9,9 aka A1 to J10
VARIABLE DKG_X
VARIABLE DKG_Y

; the x,y of the lower right 'room'
VARIABLE DKG_YMAX
VARIABLE DKG_XMAX

; destination if moving under the driver's control
VARIABLE DKG_XDEST
VARIABLE DKG_YDEST

; -1=ignore directions, 0=no need to show 'room', 1=user looked, 2=user moved
VARIABLE DKG_SHOW

; unique value for each map location to simplify comparisons
VARIABLE DKG_ID

; the room the door leads to
VARIABLE DKG_DOORTO

; which wagon are we?
VARIABLE DKG_WAGON

; which driver's bench are we?
VARIABLE DKG_DRIVER

; 0=uninitialized, 1=real room, 2=simulated room
VARIABLE DKG_STATE

; load for being stuck in rut
VARIABLE DKG_LOAD

; DUMMY2 -1=at boundary, -2=reset, -3=error reset
;   0=none, 1=n, 2=ne, 3=e, 4=se, 5=s, 6=sw, 7=w, 8=nw, 9=auto
;    1
;  8   2
;7   0   3
;  6   4
;    5

;----------------Items----------------------------
;Wagon
INUMBER 1409
NAME 885
WEIGHT 1000
VOLUME 500
CONTAINER IN
INTERIOR 500
SUBSTANCE INDESTRUCTABLE
*DESCRIPTION_START EXAMINE
The wagon is a large passenger coach. It hold a number of people and is pulled by eight spirited horses. A bench for the driver is up on top.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB GO -1
  EQUAL DUMMY1 RNUM
  AFFECT DKG_WAGON
  IFITEM 3 OPEN
    CLEARVERB
    MOVE DKG_WAGON
    AFFECT DUMMY1
    ECHO ALL %P climbs into a wagon.
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You must wait for the driver to open the door.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;Window
INUMBER 475
NAME 266
WEIGHT 1000
VOLUME 1000
CONTAINER IN
INTERIOR 500
SUBSTANCE INDESTRUCTABLE
HIDDEN
OPEN
IFPREVERB OPEN -1
  IFVAR ITEMVAL3 = 0
    ECHO PLAYER You open %a.
	ECHO OTHERS %N opens %a.
	EQUAL ITEMVAL3 1
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER The window is already open.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CLOSE -1
  IFVAR ITEMVAL3 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER You close %a.
	ECHO OTHERS %N closes %a.
	EQUAL ITEMVAL3 0
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER The window is already closed.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
; if something is put in the window
IFPREVERB2 PUT -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You throw %a out the window, where it disappears from sight.
  ECHO OTHERS %N throws %a out the window, where it disappears from sight.
  REMOVEITEM -1
  IFVAR DKG_LOAD > 0
    SUB DKG_LOAD 1
    IFVAR DKG_LOAD = 0
      EQUAL DKG_SHOW 0
      ECHO ALL The wagon creaks and pops as its weight shifts.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
