NUMBER 524
NAME Grassland, Small Rise
PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
This rise marks the southern end of the lowlands. To the south, down a rocky
trail, lay the shores of the Inner Sea. The cold wind sharply bends the grass
and sparse shrubs resting at the top of this rise, and blasts you with the rank
and bitter smell of the sea. Far to the north one can faintly see the curling
smoke from the chimneys of Fayd.
*DESCRIPTION_END
