NUMBER 1635
NAME Commercial Ferry
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are on the commercial ferry that carries goods across the river for Fayd
and other towns on the Eastern shore of the Eltinmar river. It is wide of beam
and rather square shaped. A cold wind bites you as the paddlewheels on each
side of the craft push it through the water at a good rate of speed for
something so large. The river is crowded here with various types of boats
making their way with holds full of sundry goods.
