NUMBER 1639
NAME Freight Hauler
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
Here is the western edge of Across. A large building surrounded by a wall sets
here from which freight wagons cross the empty miles to haul riches from the
west. Constructed of mud bricks, the wall surrounding the Freight Hauler is
three to five feet thick and over fifteen feet high. A large oak gate faces
back toward the plaza. It is usually kept open to allow access. This is also
