straight-backed chair, and a small table holding a few maps and books on
military theory. A brass lamp sits on the table. A beaded curtain separates
this room from the Captain's room. A door leads back out.   
*DESCRIPTION_END
CALL 33
;----------------door out-------
ITEM 0 65 VAL2=1657 CLOSED UNLOCKED
;----------------curtain-------
ITEM 1 1031 ADJ1=620 VAL2=1660
IFPREVERB GO 1
	ECHO ALL The beads clatter as you part them.
	AFFECT 1660
	ECHO ALL The beads clatter as %N parts them.	
	AFFECT 1658 
ENDIF
;------------ lamp ---------------
ITEM 2 1565 ADJ3=32 
;--------------cot----------------
ITEM 3 436 
;-------------table---------------
ITEM 4 91 
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
On the table is a map of the area around Fayd and several books on military theory.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;--------------chair--------------
ITEM 5 86 
;-------------rack---------------
ITEM 6 539 
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 6
The rack contains a well made but plain set of armor, a shield and a couple broadswords.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;-----------------------------------------
NUMBER 1659
NAME Houndsteeth Tower, Sergeant's Room 
DAY_LIGHT 
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
This room reflects the relatively spartan lifestyle of the Sergeant. The 
furnishings consist of a rough wooden bed piled with woolen blankets, a rack
for his most cherished weapons, a crate in which he keeps his two uniforms he
is not wearing at the time, and a small locked chest containing his personal
items. A brass lamp is mounted on the wall for light. An opening leads into the
armory and a door leads out.  
*DESCRIPTION_END
CALL 33
;----------------door out-------
ITEM 0 65 VAL2=1657
;----------------opening-------
ITEM 1 72 VAL2=1661 CLOSED UNLOCKED
;------------ lamp ---------------
ITEM 2 1565 ADJ3=32
;-------------rack---------------
ITEM 6 539 
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 6
The rack contains several exotic weapons that seem to be the treasures of the sergeant.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;---------------------------------------
NUMBER 1660
NAME Houndsteeth Tower, Captain's Room 
DAY_LIGHT 
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
This room contains old but comfortable furniture, a handful of personal
weapons, a good number of general interest books, a few pieces of modest art,
the Captain's clothing and toiletries, and an expensive chess set. A brass lamp
sits on a small desk. A beaded curtain separates this room from the
Lieutenant's room.
*DESCRIPTION_END
CALL 33
;----------------curtain-------
ITEM 1 1031 ADJ1=620 VAL2=1658
IFPREVERB GO 1
	ECHO ALL The beads clatter as you part them.
	AFFECT 1658
	ECHO ALL The beads clatter as %N parts them.	
	AFFECT 1660 
ENDIF
;------------ lamp ---------------
ITEM 2 1565 ADJ3=32
;-------------desk---------------
ITEM 3 201 
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
A small neat desk clean except for pictures of a woman and 2 smaller children
in simple frames and a brass lamp.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;------------------------------------
NUMBER 1661
NAME Houndsteeth Tower, Armory 
DAY_LIGHT 
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
The guards are allowed to keep short swords, knives and leather helmets with
their personal belongings in the Main Hall. Heavier weapons, missile weapons
and armor are stored here under the watchful eye of the garrison sergeant. The
armory holds enough bows, arrows, crossbows and bolts to hold off a small army
for several days, long enough for a messenger to reach Fayd and return with
reinforcements. As well it holds two dozen chainmail shirts and a like number
of small shields, spears and axes. Access is through the sergeant's quarters
and a stairs leads to the roof. A brass lamp illuminates the room.   
*DESCRIPTION_END
CALL 33
;----------------opening-------
ITEM 1 72 VAL2=1659
;------------ stairs up  ---------------
ITEM 0 81 ADJ1=492 VAL2=1662
;------------ lamp ---------------
ITEM 2 1565 ADJ3=32
;----------------------------------------
NUMBER 1662
NAME Houndsteeth Tower, Roof 
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
The keep's roof is flat on top with a crenellated wall around the edges. From
here, watcher's can see to a distance of many miles in all directions. To the
west the Trazilar River snakes to the north, while to the east the farms and 
orchards seem to go on forever. In times of need, defenders can fire missile
weapons and hurl stones from this roof to repel attackers below. Torches
mounted along the wall illuminate the area. Stairs lead back down.
*DESCRIPTION_END
CALL 33
;------------ stairs down ---------------
ITEM 1 1226 ADJ1=493 VAL2=1661
IFPREVERB GAZE -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You look down to the front of the keep.
  SHOWROOM 1653
ENDIF
;------------torches---------------
ITEM 2 373 
;-----------------------------
NUMBER 1663
NAME Houndsteeth Tower, Dungeon 
DAY_LIGHT 
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
A trapdoor leads into this room from the Main Hall above. The room contains
crude shelves and stacks of crates full of supplies, mostly foodstuffs. Drying
onions and other herbs dangle from the floor joists overhead. In the back of
this area is a detention cell. A torch is mounted in an iron bracket on the
wall. An iron door keeps prisoners secure. 
*DESCRIPTION_END
CALL 33
;-----------trapdoor-----------
ITEM 0 550 VAL2=1655 CLOSED UNLOCKED
;----------------door-------
ITEM 1 65 ADJ1=169 VAL1=99 VAL2=1664 VAL3=1664 CLOSED LOCKED
;-----------shelves-------
ITEM 2 341
;-----------crates--------
ITEM 3 1033
;------------torches---------------
ITEM 4 373
;-------------------------------------
NUMBER 1664
NAME Houndsteeth Tower, Detention Cell 
DAY_LIGHT 
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
This dark room can hold three or four prisoners in its confines. A bare earthen
floor provides the only sleeping surface. 
*DESCRIPTION_END
CALL 33
;----------------door-------
ITEM 0 65 ADJ1=169 VAL1=99 VAL2=1663 VAL3=1664 CLOSED LOCKED
;-----------------Landing---------------
NUMBER 1665
NAME Two Trees Landing
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
Here lies the river landing known as Two Trees. No trees are visible so its not
clear why its called that.
*DESCRIPTION_END
CALL 33
IFENTRY
    IFITEM 6
    	ECHO PLAYER You notice a ship tied up there.
    ENDIF
ENDIF
;------summon wagon if it's empty------------------
IFPREVERB GAZE -1
  ;if the wagon isn't here
  IFNOITEM 0
    ;add the wagon to the station
    NEWITEM 0 1409 ADJ1=222 ADJ2=355 VAL2=1667
    EQUAL DKG_STATE 1
    EQUAL DKG_X 0
    EQUAL DKG_Y 2
    EQUAL DKG_ID 2
    EQUAL DKG_LOAD 0
    AFFECT DKG_WAGON
    EQUAL DUMMY1 PLRSINROOM
    AFFECT 1665
    ; if wagon is empty
    IFVAR DUMMY1 = 0
      ;remove the wagon from any real room it may be at
      IFVAR DKG_DOORTO ! -1
        AFFECT DKG_DOORTO
        IFITEM 0
          REMOVEITEM 0
          ECHO ALL The wagon pulls away.
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
      AFFECT DKG_WAGON
      EQUAL DKG_DOORTO 1665
      SETITEMVAL 3 2 DKG_DOORTO
      UNLOCK 3
      OPEN 3
      ECHO ALL The driver opens the door and says, "This is not a usual stop, be careful."
      AFFECT 1665
      ECHO ALL %cA wagon appears from out of the distance and comes to a stop.
      ECHO ALL %cWhen it stops, the driver opens the door and says, "This is not a usual stop, be careful."
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER You look out over the land, but see no sign of the wagon.
      ECHO OTHERS %N looks out over the land.
    ENDIF
    CLEARVERB
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
; WAGON.SCR 7/14/98 modified by Amer [Randy Johnson] from script
;  by Taliesin Pendragon [David Goodman dgoodman@pacbell.net] 
;  to separate the driver from the passengers more.
;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
NUMBER 1666
NAME Coach Drivers Bench
REGION 0
CHANNEL 1666
ECHOCHAN 1667
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT

; map
ITEM 1 1306
EXTEND 1 frayed at the edges and showing its age
; bench
ITEM 2 339 ADJ1=355
EXTEND 2 of some light wood polished smooth by drivers' bottoms
; trap door to passengers area
ITEM 4 550 VAL2=1667 OPEN UNLOCKED
; man to be the driver
ITEM 5 1587
EXTEND 5 dressed in a gray duster and a broad brimmed hat

*DESCRIPTION_START
This high bench is located on top of the coach allowing the driver to see for
great distances. An old map lays on the bench. A trapdoor leads into the
passenger compartment. A man sits on the bench next to you.
*DESCRIPTION_END

;the driver
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
The driver is a short man with pale blue eyes that seem to be focused on
the horizon all the time. His hair is covered by a floppy broad-brimmed hat,
but his long drooping moustache shows his hair to be red shot with gray.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFSAY hi!
	ECHO ALL The driver nods and answers, "Howdy, they call me Lucky."
ENDIF
IFSAY hello
	ECHO ALL The driver answers, "Howdy stranger, they call me Lucky."
ENDIF
IFSAY howdy
	ECHO ALL The driver smiles and answers, "How do stranger? They call me Lucky."
ENDIF
IFSAY greetings
	ECHO ALL The driver chuckles and answers, "Well, greetings to you mi'lord, they call me Lucky."
ENDIF

;The map. Note: diagonal travel provides the most varied descriptions.
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
        A   B   C   D   E   F   G   H   I   J
   RMMM     MMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMM            MMMMMMM   A = Across Station
   RR MMMMMMMM+   +   +   +  MMMMMMMMMMMMM+   RRR  B = Houndsteeth Keep
 1 RRR                                         RR  C = Chasm
   RRR+   +   +   +   +   +   +   +   +   +   +RR  M = Mountain
 2 RRR                                         RR  R = River
   RRR+   +   +   +   +   +   +   +   +   +   +RR  S = Swamp
 3 RRRR                                        RR  T = Trail
   RRRR   +   +   +   +   +   +   +   +   +   +RR  O = Ocean
 4 RRRR                                       RR
    RR+   +   +   +   +   +   +   +   +   +   RR
 5  RR           T  T                          RR
    RR+   +   +T  +   + T +   +   +   +   +   +RR       N
 6  RR            CCCCC  T                     RR       |
   RRR+   +  T+   +   +   + T +   +   +   +   +RR    W- o -E
 7 RRRR           CCCCC       T                RR       |
   RRRR   + T +   +   +   +   + T +   +   +   +RR       S
 8 RRR            SSSSS            T           RR
   RRR+   +T  +   +   +   +   +   +  T+   +   +RR
 9 RRR            SSSSS                T      RR
   RRR+   +T  +   +   +   +   +   +   +  T+   RR
10 RRR  B T       SSSSS                     A RR Map drawn by dkg
   RRR+OOOOOOOOOO +   +   +   +   OOOOOOOOOOOORR circa 1040 Year of the Spider
   ROOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB LISTEN 2
  CLEARVERB
  STRCVT 0 DKG_X
  STRCVT 1 DKG_Y
  STRCVT 2 DKG_ID
  STRCVT 3 DKG_DOORTO
  STRCVT 4 DKG_STATE
  STRCVT 5 DKG_WAGON
  ECHO PLAYER DKG_X:%0 DKG_Y:%1 DKG_ID:%2 DKG_DOORTO:%3 DKG_STATE:%4 DKG_WAGON:%5
ENDIF

IFVERB RECALL -1
  IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
    ; If a gm tries to recall...
    IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER ...and being the smart gm you are, you recall that driver commands are:
      ECHO PLAYER "Stop!", "Where are we?" and "Go n" or "Go sw" etc.
      ECHO PLAYER If the wagon is in a rut, throw stuff out the window until DKG_LOAD is 0.
      ECHO PLAYER If the door leads to 1668 and people are in that room, the wagon won't leave.
      ECHO PLAYER At Across Station, GAZE to summon the wagon if it's empty and not there.
      CLEARVERB
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF

; start with no verbal command
EQUAL DUMMY2 0
EQUAL DUMMY4 0
EQUAL DUMMY5 0

; process verbal commands
IFSAY Go_n
  EQUAL DUMMY2 1
  EQUAL DUMMY5 -1
ENDIF
IFSAY Go_ne
  EQUAL DUMMY2 2
  EQUAL DUMMY5 -1
  EQUAL DUMMY4 1
ENDIF
IFSAY Go_e
  EQUAL DUMMY2 3
  EQUAL DUMMY4 1
ENDIF
IFSAY Go_se
  EQUAL DUMMY2 4
  EQUAL DUMMY5 1
  EQUAL DUMMY4 1
ENDIF
IFSAY Go_s
  EQUAL DUMMY2 5
  EQUAL DUMMY5 1
ENDIF
IFSAY Go_sw
  EQUAL DUMMY2 6
  EQUAL DUMMY5 1
  EQUAL DUMMY4 -1
ENDIF
IFSAY Go_w
  EQUAL DUMMY2 7
  EQUAL DUMMY4 -1
ENDIF
IFSAY Go_nw
  EQUAL DUMMY2 8
  EQUAL DUMMY4 -1
  EQUAL DUMMY5 -1
ENDIF
IFSAY Where_are_we?
  IFVAR DKG_X = 0
    STRCPY 0 "grid_A
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 1
    STRCPY 0 "grid_B
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 2
    STRCPY 0 "grid_C
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 3
    STRCPY 0 "grid_D
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 4
    STRCPY 0 "grid_E
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 5
    STRCPY 0 "grid_F
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 6
    STRCPY 0 "grid_G
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 7
    STRCPY 0 "grid_H
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 8
    STRCPY 0 "grid_I
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 9
    STRCPY 0 "grid_J
  ENDIF
  EQUAL DUMMY1 DKG_Y
  ADD DUMMY1 1
  STRCVT 1 DUMMY1
  ECHO ALL The driver says, "We're at map %0%1."
ENDIF
IFSAY Stop!
  ;Don't allow arbitrary stops at real rooms. Can this be consolidated with station arrival?
  IFVAR DKG_DOORTO = -1
    EQUAL DKG_DOORTO 1668
    EQUAL DKG_STATE 1
    AFFECT DKG_WAGON
    SETITEMVAL 3 2 1668
    UNLOCK 3
    OPEN 3
    ECHO ALL The driver unlatches the door and says, "Stay by the wagon."
    AFFECT DKG_DOORTO
    ;add the old wooden wagon to the station
    NEWITEM 0 1409 ADJ1=222 ADJ2=355 VAL2=1667
    ECHO ALL A wagon arrives.
    AFFECT DKG_DRIVER
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;---reset (lick bench)-----
IFPREVERB LICK 2
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
  	EQUAL DUMMY2 -2
  	CLEARVERB
  ENDIF
ENDIF

;test for bad variables
IFVAR DUMMY2 < -1
  EQUAL DUMMY2 -3
ENDIF
IFVAR DUMMY2 > 9
  EQUAL DUMMY2 -3
ENDIF
IFVAR DKG_SHOW < -1
  EQUAL DUMMY2 -3
ENDIF
IFVAR DKG_SHOW > 2
  EQUAL DUMMY2 -3
ENDIF
IFVAR DKG_X < 0
  EQUAL DUMMY2 -3
ENDIF
IFVAR DKG_X > 9
  EQUAL DUMMY2 -3
ENDIF
IFVAR DKG_Y < 0
  EQUAL DUMMY2 -3
ENDIF
IFVAR DKG_Y > 9
  EQUAL DUMMY2 -3
ENDIF
IFVAR DKG_WAGON ! 1667
  EQUAL DUMMY2 -3
ENDIF
IFVAR DKG_DRIVER ! 1666
  EQUAL DUMMY2 -3
ENDIF
IFVAR DKG_DOORTO < -1
  EQUAL DUMMY2 -3
ENDIF
IFVAR DKG_DOORTO > 1668
  EQUAL DUMMY2 -3
ENDIF
IFVAR DKG_LOAD < 0
  EQUAL DUMMY2 -3
ENDIF
IFVAR DKG_LOAD > 100
  EQUAL DUMMY2 -3
ENDIF
IFVAR DKG_STATE < 0
  EQUAL DUMMY2 -3
ENDIF
IFVAR DKG_STATE > 2
  EQUAL DUMMY2 -3
ENDIF

IFVAR DUMMY2 < -1
  ; force initialize
  IFVAR DUMMY2 = -3
    ECHO ALL The driver seems ill.
  ENDIF
  ECHO ALL The driver suddenly races the wagon at breakneck speed until it ends up at a station.
  EQUAL DKG_DOORTO 1639
  AFFECT 1667
  SETITEMVAL 3 2 DKG_DOORTO
  UNLOCK 3
  OPEN 3
  EQUAL DKG_STATE 1
  EQUAL DKG_LOAD 0
  EQUAL DKG_YMAX 9
  EQUAL DKG_XMAX 9
  EQUAL DKG_X DKG_XMAX
  EQUAL DKG_Y DKG_YMAX
  EQUAL DKG_XDEST -1
  EQUAL DKG_YDEST -1
  EQUAL DKG_WAGON 1667
  EQUAL DKG_DRIVER 1666
  EQUAL DKG_SHOW 0
  EQUAL DUMMY2 0
  AFFECT DKG_DRIVER
ENDIF

; see if we're under the driver's control
IFVAR DUMMY2 = 0
  IFVAR DKG_YDEST ! -1
    EQUAL DUMMY2 9
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_XDEST ! -1
    EQUAL DUMMY2 9
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY2 = 9
    IFVAR DKG_XDEST > DKG_X
      EQUAL DUMMY4 1
    ELSE
      IFVAR DKG_XDEST < DKG_X
        EQUAL DUMMY4 -1
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DKG_YDEST > DKG_Y
      EQUAL DUMMY5 1
    ELSE
      IFVAR DKG_YDEST < DKG_Y
        EQUAL DUMMY5 -1
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY4 = 0
      IFVAR DUMMY5 = 0
        ECHO ALL The driver says, "We have arrived."
        EQUAL DKG_XDEST -1
        EQUAL DKG_YDEST -1
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF

; handle motion commands here if already moving or stuck in a rut
IFVAR DUMMY2 > 0
  IFVAR DKG_SHOW = -1
    EQUAL DUMMY2 0
    IFVAR DKG_LOAD > 0
      ECHO ALL The driver calls to the horses, but the wagon doesn't budge from the rut it's in.
    ELSE
      ECHO ALL The driver loudly says, "I am busy right now driving, hold on to your horses."
      STRCVT 0 ROUNDTIME
      ECHO PLAYER [Wait %0 seconds...]
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF

;test boundaries
IFVAR DUMMY2 > 0
  ;northish
  IFVAR DUMMY5 = -1
    IFVAR DKG_Y < 1
      EQUAL DUMMY2 -1
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  ;southish
  IFVAR DUMMY5 = 1
    IFVAR DKG_Y = DKG_YMAX
      EQUAL DUMMY2 -1
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  ;eastish
  IFVAR DUMMY4 = 1
    IFVAR DKG_X = DKG_XMAX
      EQUAL DUMMY2 -1
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  ;westish
  IFVAR DUMMY4 = -1
    IFVAR DKG_X < 1
      EQUAL DUMMY2 -1
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF

;test if leaving, with people at a stop
IFVAR DUMMY2 > 0
  IFVAR DKG_DOORTO = 1668
    AFFECT DKG_DOORTO
    IFVAR PLRSINROOM ! 0
      ECHO ALL The driver says, "The wagon is leaving. All aboard!"
      AFFECT DKG_WAGON
      ECHO ALL The driver says, "We're not leaving until everyone has come back in."
      EQUAL DUMMY2 -1
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  AFFECT DKG_WAGON
ENDIF

;default to not showing the window view if we're not moving
IFVAR DKG_SHOW ! -1
  EQUAL DKG_SHOW 0
ENDIF

IFVAR DUMMY2 = -1
  ECHO ALL The driver says, "The coach won't go any further in that direction."
  EQUAL DUMMY2 0
ENDIF

;leave current location if possible
IFVAR DUMMY2 > 0
  ; calculate new room
  ADD DKG_X DUMMY4
  ADD DKG_Y DUMMY5

  ; combine coordinates into a unique number to make comparisons easier
  EQUAL DUMMY1 DKG_X
  MULT DUMMY1 10
  ADD DUMMY1 DKG_Y

  ; test new room here (note: don't put obstacles next to a station)
  ; if that direction is grid D7, D8, D9, D10...
  IFVAR DKG_X = 3
	IFVAR DKG_Y > 4
    		ECHO ALL The driver points at the obstacle and says, "We can't go in that direction."
    		; back out the motion
    		SUB DKG_X DUMMY4
    		SUB DKG_Y DUMMY5
  
  	ELSE
    		;are we leaving a real room with the door open?
    		;the doorto test won't be necessary once we close the doors again
    		IFVAR DKG_DOORTO ! -1
      		AFFECT DKG_WAGON
      		IFITEM 3 OPEN
        			EQUAL DKG_STATE 2
        			ECHO ALL The driver secures the door from the outside.
        			CLOSE 3
        			LOCK 3
        			SETITEMVAL 3 2 -1
        			AFFECT DKG_DOORTO
        			ECHO ALL The wagon pulls away.
        			REMOVEITEM 0
        			AFFECT DKG_WAGON
        			EQUAL DKG_DOORTO -1
      		ENDIF
      		AFFECT DKG_DRIVER
    		ENDIF

    		EQUAL DKG_ID DUMMY1
    		; show new scene
    		EQUAL DKG_SHOW 2
  	ENDIF
  ELSE
 	;are we leaving a real room with the door open?
    	;the doorto test won't be necessary once we close the doors again
    	IFVAR DKG_DOORTO ! -1
      	AFFECT DKG_WAGON
      	IFITEM 3 OPEN
      		EQUAL DKG_STATE 2
      		ECHO ALL The driver secures the door from the outside.
      		CLOSE 3
      		LOCK 3
      		SETITEMVAL 3 2 -1
      		AFFECT DKG_DOORTO
      		ECHO ALL The wagon pulls away.
      		REMOVEITEM 0
      		AFFECT DKG_WAGON
      		EQUAL DKG_DOORTO -1
      	ENDIF
      	AFFECT DKG_DRIVER
    	ENDIF

    	EQUAL DKG_ID DUMMY1
    	; show new scene
    	EQUAL DKG_SHOW 2
  ENDIF
ENDIF

;look out the window
IFPREVERB GAZE -1
  CLEARVERB
  ; show current scene
  EQUAL DKG_SHOW 1
ENDIF

; if we're showing a scene
IFVAR DKG_SHOW > 0
  ; see if we're moving
  IFVAR DKG_SHOW = 2
    RANDOM DUMMY1 1 4 0
    IFVAR DUMMY1 = 1
      ECHO ALL The driver calls to the horses, and as the coach creaks along you see the landscape shift beyond the window:%c
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY1 = 2
      ECHO ALL The land slides under the coach as the horses pull it along at the driver's urging:%c
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY1 = 3
      ECHO ALL As the driver guides the horses you see a changing environment outside the window:%c
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY1 = 4
      ECHO ALL The view reveals a scene shifting with the motion of the coach:%c
    ENDIF
  ENDIF

  ;Set terrain based on longitude
  IFVAR DKG_X = 0
    STRCPY 3 "land_bounded_by_a_broad_river_to_the_west._The_area_is_empty,
    ; STRCPY 0 "steep,_treacherous_cliffs_and_trails_and_tall_mountains_cutting_you_off_from_travel_west._The_area_is_empty,
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 1
    STRCPY 3 "rolling_hills_devoid_of_settlements,
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 2
    STRCPY 3 "a_bumpy_plain,_rising_to_the_west,
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 3
    STRCPY 3 "a_flat,_barren_expanse
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 4
    STRCPY 3 "a_deserted,_lonely_landscape
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 5
    STRCPY 3 "an_inhospitable_wasteland
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 6
    STRCPY 3 "many_deep_cracks_and_sinkholes_in_the_land,
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 7
    STRCPY 3 "plateaus_and_deep_chasms
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 8
    STRCPY 3 "dried_up,_rubble_filled_riverbeds
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_X = 9
    STRCPY 3 "swampy_land_bounded_by_a_raging_river_to_the_east,
  ENDIF

  ;Set greenery based on latitude
  IFVAR DKG_Y = 0
    STRCPY 1 "with_deep_ruts_to_trap_the_errant_coach.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_Y = 1
    STRCPY 1 "with_only_a_few_scattered_bushes_nearby,_their_limbs_twisted_oddly.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_Y = 2
    STRCPY 1 "with_few_trees_and_little_other_vegetation.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_Y = 3
    STRCPY 1 "populated_by_tall_trees_that_bear_no_fruit.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_Y = 4
    STRCPY 1 "displaying_nothing_of_interest_to_break_the_tedium.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_Y = 5
    STRCPY 1 "barren_of_life._Yet,_for_some_reason_the_horses_seem_uneasy.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_Y = 6
    STRCPY 1 "home_only_to_the_circling_scavengers._They_seem_to_be_eyeing_you_hungrily.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_Y = 7
    STRCPY 1 "unmoving_except_for_the_slither_of_reptiles.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_Y = 8
    STRCPY 1 "offering_no_shelter_from_the_elements.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DKG_Y = 9
    STRCPY 1 "with_only_swampland_and_bugs_for_company.
  ENDIF

  ;set third value from the location (set the modulo to the number of selections)
  EQUAL DUMMY3 DKG_ID
  MOD DUMMY3 13

  ;select the third element with fixed location
  IFVAR DUMMY3 = 0
    STRCPY 2 "An_unexpected_cracking_sound_is_emitted_by_the_coach's_frame_as_it_dips_into_a_rut
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY3 = 1
    STRCPY 2 "Bleached_bones_lay_strewn_about_near_a_rockslide
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY3 = 2
    STRCPY 2 "The_coach_lurches_queasily_as_it_negotiates_a_hazard
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY3 = 3
    STRCPY 2 "A_smell_of_rotted_flesh_on_the_breeze_creeps_into_the_coach
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY3 = 4
    STRCPY 2 "Behind_you_the_wind_seems_to_be_erasing_your_trail
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY3 = 5
    STRCPY 2 "Buzzing_insects_fly_in_the_window_with_annoying_frequency_here
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY3 = 6
    STRCPY 2 "Foul_smelling_air_rises_from_the_ground,_but_no_source_of_odor_can_be_seen
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY3 = 7
    STRCPY 2 "The_rotting_remains_of_an_abandoned_wagon_can_be_seen_in_the_distance
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY3 = 8
    STRCPY 2 "This_spot_seems_to_appeal_to_the_horses_as_a_nice_place_to_relieve_themselves
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY3 = 9
    STRCPY 2 "There_is_a_thundering_rumble_getting_louder,_but_you_see_no_sign_of_its_cause
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY3 = 10
    STRCPY 2 "A_dust_cloud_in_the_distance_approaches_threateningly
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY3 = 11
    STRCPY 2 "Carrion_birds_sit_perched_on_the_darkened_limb_of_a_dead_tree_nearby,_appraising_you_as_you_pass
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY3 = 12
    STRCPY 2 "An_illegible_tombstone_marks_the_site_of_a_fallen_traveller
  ENDIF

  ; about every 7th move, add an extra phrase.
  RANDOM DUMMY1 1 7 0
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 1
    RANDOM DUMMY3 1 6 0
    IFVAR DUMMY3 = 1
      STRCAT 2 ".%c%cA_low_moan_escapes_the_driver,_but_he_continues_steadfastly_on_without_explanation
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY3 = 2
      STRCAT 2 ".%c%cIn_the_distance_the_cry_of_an_animal_is_cut_short_suddenly
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY3 = 3
      STRCAT 2 ".%c%cA_small_animal_scurries_away_from_the_coach_in_fear
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY3 = 4
      STRCAT 2 ".%c%cThe_driver_seems_to_be_wary_of_something_here._Drawing_his_gun,_he_shoots_at_something_unseen
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY3 = 5
      STRCAT 2 ".%c%cThere's_an_unexpected_jolt_and_something_falls,_landing_with_a_crash_but_quickly_lost_from_sight.
      ; STRCAT 2 ".%c%cThere's_an_unexpected_jolt_and_something_falls_from_the_wagon,_landing_with_a_crash_but_quickly_lost_from_sight.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUMMY3 = 6
      STRCAT 2 ".%c%cSuddenly,_the_door_latch_gives_way_and_it_swings_wide_open._The_driver_slams_it_shut_with_a_curse
    ENDIF
  ENDIF

  ; if someone looks
  IFVAR DKG_SHOW = 1
    ; if it's a real room and not simulated
    IFVAR DKG_STATE = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You gaze out the window:%c%c
      SHOWROOM DKG_DOORTO
    ; else if it's a simulated room
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER You gaze out the window:%c%c[The Wastes]%cYou see %3 %1 %2.%c
    ENDIF

  ; else if we moved
  ELSE
    ; if it's a real room and not simulated
    IFVAR DKG_STATE = 1
      ; use the room the door leads to
      ECHO ALL The window shows:%c
      SHOWROOM DKG_DOORTO
    ELSE
      ; if it's simulated
      ECHO ALL [The Wastes]%cYou see %3 %1 %2.
    ENDIF

    EQUAL DKG_SHOW -1
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 3
    ; ECHO PLAYER [Round: 10 sec]
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ; after delay, driver accepts commands again
    EQUAL DKG_SHOW 2

    ; is this affected by the roundtime? ???
    ;test for arrival at a station
    IFVAR DKG_ID = 99
      ; use the state temporarily to note the station
      EQUAL DKG_STATE 1639
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DKG_ID = 9
      EQUAL DKG_STATE 1652
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DKG_ID = 2
      EQUAL DKG_STATE 1665
    ENDIF    
    IFVAR DKG_STATE > 1600
      EQUAL DKG_DOORTO DKG_STATE
      EQUAL DKG_STATE 1
      AFFECT DKG_WAGON
      SETITEMVAL 3 2 DKG_DOORTO
      UNLOCK 3
      OPEN 3
      AFFECT DKG_DOORTO
      ;add the wagon to the station
      NEWITEM 0 1409 ADJ1=222 ADJ2=355 VAL2=1667
      ECHO ALL A wagon arrives in a cloud of dust, the horses panting and snorting.
      ECHO ALL %cWhen it rolls to a stop the driver unlatches the door and says, "We've arrived at a wagon station."
      AFFECT DKG_DRIVER
      ECHO ALL The driver unlatches the door and says, "We've arrived at a wagon station."
    ENDIF
    ECHO ALL %cThe driver asks for new directions.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
NUMBER 1667
NAME A horse-drawn coach
REGION 0
CHANNEL 1667
ECHOCHAN 1666
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT

; window
ITEM 0 475 VAL2=1639
; bench
ITEM 2 339 ADJ1=355
EXTEND 2 of some light wood polished smooth by passengers' bottoms
; a door (should be latchable and impervious/unseepable)
ITEM 3 350 VAL2=1639 ADJ1=355 OPEN UNLOCKED
;  trapdoor to drivers bench
ITEM 4 550 VAL2=1666 OPEN UNLOCKED

*DESCRIPTION_START
This enclosed wooden coach is drawn by a sturdy team of eight strong horses.
Built into the sides are windows through which you can see the world outside.
Wooden benches have been set in rows for the passengers. There is a trapdoor
that leads up to the drivers bench.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFENTRY
  ; put player in Across station if script used for first time since loading
  ; let station initialize everything
  IFVAR DKG_STATE = 0
    ECHO PLAYER The driver says, "No stowaways!" and pushes you out the door.
    MOVE 1639
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER The coach creaks as you enter the wagon.
    ECHO OTHERS The coach creaks as %p enters the wagon.
  ENDIF
ENDIF

;look out the window
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  CLEARVERB
  ; show current scene
  EQUAL DKG_SHOW 1
ENDIF

; if someone looks
IFVAR DKG_SHOW = 1
; if it's a real room and not simulated
    IFVAR DKG_STATE = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You gaze out the window:%c%c
      SHOWROOM DKG_DOORTO
; else if it's a simulated room
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER You gaze out the window:%c%c[The Wastes]%cYou see %3 %1 %2.%c
    ENDIF
    EQUAL DKG_SHOW 0
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 4
	CLEARVERB
	AFFECT DKG_DRIVER
	IFVAR PLRSINROOM < 1
		AFFECT DKG_WAGON
		ECHO ALL %N crawls through the trap door, up onto the bench next to the driver.
		MOVE DKG_DRIVER
		POSITION SIT
		AFFECT DKG_DRIVER
		ECHO ALL The driver tips his hat to %N.
		AFFECT DKG_WAGON
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
NUMBER 1668
NAME The Wastes
REGION 0
CHANNEL 1
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT

; wagon
ITEM 0 1409 ADJ1=222 ADJ2=355 VAL2=1666

*DESCRIPTION_START
All that can be seen in any direction is desolate wasteland.
Any attempt to explore is prevented by the driver.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFENTRY
  ; gen ticks
  IFVAR MONINROOM < 3
    GENMON 166
  ENDIF

  IFNOITEM 0
    ECHO PLAYER Hmmm... there's no wagon here. Now what are you gonna do?
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB DROP -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The driver keeps you from littering here.
  ECHO OTHERS The driver glares at %n about something.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SEARCH -1
  RANDOM DUMMY1 1 3 0
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER You find a rock.
    NEWITEM 1 829
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 3
    ; ECHO PLAYER [Round: 10 sec]
    CLEARVERB
  ENDIF
ENDIF

;Are all aboard?
IFVAR PLRSINROOM = 0
  REMOVEITEM 0

  AFFECT DKG_WAGON
  ECHO ALL The driver secures the door from the outside and says, "Everyone is back on board. Which way shall we go?"
  CLOSE 3
  LOCK 3
  SETITEMVAL 3 2 -1
  EQUAL DKG_STATE 2
ENDIF
;------------------ CEvent May 1998 --------------
;
;set the time interval to every 15 seconds
CEVENT 23 5 1634
;
;Put the timers in action
;
ADD COMMFERRY 1
ADD ACROSSMIN 1
;
;---------------------Moving the Commercial ferry---------------------
;
;------------ if ferry location gets to 13 reset it to 1 -------------
IFVAR COMMFERRY > 12
  EQUAL COMMFERRY 1
ENDIF
;
;----------------------Prepare to leave eastern dock-----
IFVAR COMMFERRY = 1
    AFFECT 1634
    ECHO ALL The ferry's cargo master yells from the wide, floating platform, "All aboard!" and the deck hands make ready to lift the gangplank.
    AFFECT 1635
    ECHO ALL The ferry's cargo master yells, "All aboard!" and the deck hands make ready to lift the gangplank.
ENDIF
;---------------------Leave eastern dock-----------------
IFVAR COMMFERRY = 2
    AFFECT 1634
    ECHO ALL With loud grunts, the deck hands lift the gangplank and the bosun signals the Bridge, suddenly the paddle wheels on each side of the ferry start to churn the water and the ferry leaves the dock.
    REMOVEITEM 6
    AFFECT 1635
    ECHO ALL With loud grunts, the deck hands lift the gangplank and the bosun signals the Bridge, suddenly the paddle wheels on each side of the ferry start to churn the water and the ferry leaves the dock.
    REMOVEITEM 6
    AFFECT 1636
    ECHO ALL The ferry seems to have begun to move away from the eastern bank of the river.
ENDIF
;-------------------move west toward the middle of river------
IFVAR COMMFERRY = 3
    AFFECT 1635
    ECHO ALL Straining against the current, the paddle wheels churning the water, the ferry heads westward across the broad river, avoiding passing boats.
    AFFECT 1634
    ECHO ALL From the dock, you can see the ferry make its way out into the current of the slow-moving river, heading to the western bank.
    AFFECT 1636
    ECHO ALL You see the ferry in the distance, making its way out into the current of the slow-moving river, heading toward you.
ENDIF
;-----------------------arrive at middle of river-------------
IFVAR COMMFERRY = 4
    AFFECT 1635
    RANDOM RIVEREVENTS 1 10 0
    IFVAR RIVEREVENTS = 1
    	ECHO ALL With a lurch, the ferry turns just in time to avoid a floating snag.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR RIVEREVENTS = 2
    	ECHO ALL With a lurch, the ferry turns just in time to avoid a fishing boat.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR RIVEREVENTS > 2
    	ECHO ALL The ferry is at mid river now, headed west.
    ENDIF
    AFFECT 1634
    ECHO ALL The ferry is mid-river now, heading to the western bank.
    AFFECT 1636
    ECHO ALL The ferry is mid-river now, heading toward you.
ENDIF
;---------------------approach the western side of river-----
IFVAR COMMFERRY = 5
    AFFECT 1635
    ECHO ALL Under the sure hand of the ferry pilot, the wooden craft begins to approach the western bank of the river.
    AFFECT 1634
    ECHO ALL You see the ferry begin to approach the western dock of the river.
    AFFECT 1636
    ECHO ALL The ferry begins its approach toward the dock you are standing on, moving out of the current of the middle of the river.
ENDIF
;---------------------dock on western side-----------------
IFVAR COMMFERRY = 6
  AFFECT 1636
  ECHO ALL The ferry bumps up against the short dock with the grinding sound of wood on wood. The deck hands drop a short gangplank.
  NEWITEM 6 412 ADJ1=290 ADJ2=355 VAL2=1635
  AFFECT 1635
  ECHO ALL With a jolt, the ferry bumps up against the short dock on the western side of the Eltinmar. The deck hands drop a short wooden gangplank.
  NEWITEM 6 412 ADJ1=290 ADJ2=355 VAL2=1636
  AFFECT 1634
  ECHO ALL The ferry seems to have made shore on the opposite side of the river.
ENDIF
;-------------------prepare to leave western dock-----------
IFVAR COMMFERRY = 7
    AFFECT 1636
    ECHO ALL The ferry's cargo master yells from the wide, floating platform, "All aboard!" and the deck hands make ready to lift the gangplank.
    AFFECT 1635
    ECHO ALL The ferry's cargo master yells, "All aboard!" and the deck hands make ready to lift the gangplank.
ENDIF
;-------------------leave western dock---------------------
IFVAR COMMFERRY = 8
    AFFECT 1636
    ECHO ALL With loud grunts, the deck hands lift the gangplank and the bosun signals the Bridge, suddenly the paddle wheels on each side of the ferry start to churn the water and the ferry leaves the dock.
    REMOVEITEM 6
    AFFECT 1635
    ECHO ALL With loud grunts, the deck hands lift the gangplank and the bosun signals the Bridge, suddenly the paddle wheels on each side of the ferry start to churn the water and the ferry leaves the dock.
    REMOVEITEM 6
    AFFECT 1634
    ECHO ALL The ferry seems to have begun to move away from the western bank of the river.
ENDIF
;------------------heading east toward middle of river------
IFVAR COMMFERRY = 9
    AFFECT 1635
    ECHO ALL Straining against the current, the paddle wheels churning the water, the ferry heads eastward across the broad river, avoiding passing cargo boats.
    AFFECT 1636
    ECHO ALL From the dock, you can see the ferry make its way out into the current of the slow-moving river, heading to the eastern bank.
    AFFECT 1634
    ECHO ALL You see the ferry in the distance, making its way out into the current of the slow-moving river, heading toward you.
ENDIF
;------------------middle of river--------------------------
IFVAR COMMFERRY = 10
    AFFECT 1635
    RANDOM RIVEREVENTS 1 10 0
    IFVAR RIVEREVENTS = 1
    	ECHO ALL With a shrill whistle, the ferry turns just in time to avoid a fisherman's boat.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR RIVEREVENTS = 2
    	ECHO ALL With a lurch, the ferry turns just in time to avoid a sandbar.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR RIVEREVENTS > 2
    	ECHO ALL The ferry is at mid river now, headed east.
    ENDIF
    AFFECT 1636
    ECHO ALL The ferry is mid-river now, heading to the eastern bank.
    AFFECT 1634
    ECHO ALL The ferry is mid-river now, heading toward you.
ENDIF
;------------------approaching eastern bank----------------
IFVAR COMMFERRY = 11
    AFFECT 1635
    ECHO ALL Under the sure hand of the ferry pilot, the wooden craft begins to approach the eastern bank of the river.
    AFFECT 1636
    ECHO ALL You see the ferry begin to approach the eastern dock of the river.
    AFFECT 1634
    ECHO ALL The ferry begins its approach toward the dock you are standing on, moving out of the current of the middle of the river.
ENDIF
;-----------------dock on eastern side--------------------
IFVAR COMMFERRY = 12
  AFFECT 1634
  ECHO ALL The ferry bumps up against the short dock with the grinding sound of wood on wood. The deck hands drop a short gangplank.
  NEWITEM 6 412 ADJ1=290 ADJ2=355 VAL2=1635
  AFFECT 1635
  ECHO ALL With a jolt, the ferry bumps up against the short dock on the eastern side of the Eltinmar. The deck hands drop a short wooden gangplank.
  NEWITEM 6 412 ADJ1=290 ADJ2=355 VAL2=1634
  AFFECT 1636
  ECHO ALL The ferry seems to have made shore on the opposite side of the river.
ENDIF
;
;-----------Define the 1 minute events in Across-------------
IFVAR ACROSSMIN > 3
;---------------Docks-------------
	RANDOM DOCKSEVENTS 1 10 0
 	IFVAR DOCKSEVENTS = 1
		AFFECT 1634
		ECHO ALL A fish jumps in the river beside the dock.
		AFFECT 1636
		ECHO ALL A fish jumps in the river beside the dock.
		AFFECT 1635
		ECHO ALL The ferry sways from side to side from wave action.
		AFFECT 555
		ECHO ALL A fish jumps in the river.
		AFFECT 556
		ECHO ALL A fish jumps in the river.
		AFFECT 557
		ECHO ALL A fish jumps in the river.
		AFFECT 558
		ECHO ALL A fish jumps in the river.			
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR DOCKSEVENTS = 2
		AFFECT 1634
		ECHO ALL You smell the damp smells of the river here.
		AFFECT 1636
		ECHO ALL The smells and sounds from the Across plaza drift to you from the west.
		AFFECT 1635
		ECHO ALL A fish jumps in the river beside the ferry.
		AFFECT 555
		ECHO ALL A cold wind blows across the river.
		AFFECT 556
		ECHO ALL A cold wind blows across the river.
		AFFECT 557
		ECHO ALL A cold wind blows across the river.
		AFFECT 558
		ECHO ALL A cold wind blows across the river.		
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR DOCKSEVENTS = 3
		AFFECT 1634
		ECHO ALL A couple of docks workers go by carrying large pots of garbage.
		AFFECT 1636
		ECHO ALL A fisherman prepares his small boat for a trip out into the river.
		AFFECT 1635
		ECHO ALL The ferry rocks from the current.
		AFFECT 555
		ECHO ALL Dead cattails wave in the breeze.
		AFFECT 556
		ECHO ALL Dead cattails wave in the breeze.
		AFFECT 557
		ECHO ALL Dead cattails wave in the breeze.
		AFFECT 558
		ECHO ALL Dead cattails wave in the breeze.		
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR DOCKSEVENTS = 4
		AFFECT 1634
		ECHO ALL A couple of merchants waiting for the ferry argue over the price of silk.
		AFFECT 1636
		ECHO ALL A desert nomad stands staring at the river.
		AFFECT 1635
		ECHO ALL A seagull circles the ferry looking for a snack.
		AFFECT 555
		ECHO ALL An eagle dives with a screech and snatches a fat fish from the river.
		AFFECT 556
		ECHO ALL An eagle dives with a screech and snatches a fat fish from the river.
		AFFECT 557
		ECHO ALL An eagle dives with a screech and snatches a fat fish from the river.
		AFFECT 558
		ECHO ALL An eagle dives with a screech and snatches a fat fish from the river.		
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR DOCKSEVENTS = 5
		AFFECT 1634
		ECHO ALL The hot smell of the desert blows in from the west.
		AFFECT 1636
		ECHO ALL A cart loaded with wood rumbles west.
		AFFECT 1635
		ECHO ALL Water drips from the paddle wheels.
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR DOCKSEVENTS = 6
		AFFECT 1634
		ECHO ALL You notice ice floating by.
		AFFECT 1636
		ECHO ALL You notice ice floating by.
		AFFECT 1635
		ECHO ALL An eagle dives with a screech and snatches a fat fish from the river.
	ENDIF		
;---------------Across Plaza-------------
	RANDOM ACROSSPLAZA 1 10 0
 	IFVAR ACROSSPLAZA = 1
		AFFECT 1637
		ECHO ALL The murmur of voices in many languages assault your ears.
		AFFECT 1644
		ECHO ALL The murmur of voices in many languages assault your ears.
		AFFECT 1645
		ECHO ALL Momar polishes some brass vases and bowls with a dirty rag.
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR ACROSSPLAZA = 2
		AFFECT 1637
		ECHO ALL A camel brays to the west.
		AFFECT 1644
		ECHO ALL A garrison trooper speaks to a dancing girl in one corner and she laughs.
		AFFECT 1645
		ECHO ALL A woman completely lost in her shapeless robe argues with Momar over the price of a small lamp.
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR ACROSSPLAZA = 3
		AFFECT 1637
		ECHO ALL The aroma of spiced coffee drifts from a nearby opening.
		AFFECT 1644
		ECHO ALL The bartender finishes brewing a pot of spicy coffee favored by the desert riders.
		AFFECT 1645
		ECHO ALL Momar places small trinkets on the shelves.
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR ACROSSPLAZA = 4
		AFFECT 1637
		ECHO ALL A couple of merchants entering Momar's Emporium are heard to argue over the cost of rare silkworms.
		AFFECT 1644
		ECHO ALL A caravan driver suggests that the bartender's parents were brother and sister.
		AFFECT 1645
		ECHO ALL Momar chases a small boy out of the store after he spots the youth trying to swipe a small knife.
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR ACROSSPLAZA = 5
		AFFECT 1637
		ECHO ALL The smell of fireplaces swirl around you.
		AFFECT 1644
		ECHO ALL A man in a black desert robe sits smoking a pipe in a corner.
		AFFECT 1645
		ECHO ALL Momar leans on the counter and watches the customers.
	ENDIF
;---------------Freight Hauler Courtyard---------------
	RANDOM CARAVANCOURT 1 10 0
 	IFVAR CARAVANCOURT = 1
		AFFECT 1640
		ECHO ALL The murmur of voices in many languages assault your ears.
		AFFECT 1647
		ECHO ALL A horse watches you nervously.
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR CARAVANCOURT = 2
		AFFECT 1640
		ECHO ALL A mule brays from an enclosure where it is penned up.
		AFFECT 1647
		ECHO ALL A young horse playfully runs across the stableyard.
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR CARAVANCOURT = 3
		AFFECT 1640
		ECHO ALL The aroma of horse and mule dung makes you wince.
		AFFECT 1647
		ECHO ALL A mule stoiclly chews some oats.
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR CARAVANCOURT = 4
		AFFECT 1640
		ECHO ALL A couple of men completely covered in white robes pass you by, their dark eyes evaluating your skills.
		AFFECT 1647
		ECHO ALL A blacksmith and his apprentice examine the shoes on a horse.
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR CARAVANCOURT = 5
		AFFECT 1640
		ECHO ALL The smell of the desert blows in from the west.
	ENDIF
;---------------Riverview and Houndsteeth Towers---------------
	RANDOM HOUNDSTEETH 1 10 0
 	IFVAR HOUNDSTEETH = 1
		AFFECT 1641
		IFVAR DAY = 1
    			ECHO ALL The Royal Faydian Banner flies proudly from the ramparts of the tower.
  		ELSE
    			ECHO ALL Torches move on the roof of the tower as the guards keep watch. 
  		ENDIF
		AFFECT 1642
		ECHO ALL The smell of dirty laundry is strong under one of the bunks.
		AFFECT 1652
		IFVAR DAY = 1
    			ECHO ALL The Royal Faydian Banner flies proudly from the ramparts of the tower.
  		ELSE
    			ECHO ALL Torches move on the roof of the tower as the guards keep watch. 
  		ENDIF
		AFFECT 1656
		ECHO ALL The smell of dirty laundry is strong under one of the bunks.
		AFFECT 1653
		ECHO ALL Workers are preparing the olive presses.
		AFFECT 1662
		IFVAR DAY = 1
    			ECHO ALL Far away you hear a the howl of a wolf.
  		ELSE
    			ECHO ALL Bats flutter around the torches. 
  		ENDIF 
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR HOUNDSTEETH = 2
		AFFECT 1641
		IFVAR DAY = 1
    			ECHO ALL You see the sunlight glinting off the river to your east.
  		ELSE
    			ECHO ALL Beyond the twinkling lights of Across you can just make out the glint of moonlight on the river. 
  		ENDIF
		AFFECT 1642
		ECHO ALL An old garrison cat slinks from dark corner to dark corner.
		AFFECT 1652
		IFVAR DAY = 1
    			ECHO ALL You see the sunlight glinting off the river to your west.
  		ELSE
    			ECHO ALL You can just make out the glint of moonlight on the river. 
  		ENDIF
		AFFECT 1656
		ECHO ALL An old garrison cat slinks from dark corner to dark corner.
		AFFECT 1653
		ECHO ALL The blacksmith pounds out a horseshoe while his apprentice punps the bellows.
		AFFECT 1662
		IFVAR DAY = 1
    			ECHO ALL You hear voices from below.
  		ELSE
    			ECHO ALL Moonlight glints off the river. 
  		ENDIF 
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR HOUNDSTEETH = 3
		AFFECT 1641
		ECHO ALL The sound of voices can be heard from inside the tower.
		AFFECT 1652
		ECHO ALL The sound of voices can be heard from inside the tower.
		AFFECT 1666
		ECHO ALL A courier thunders by on his way toward distant Fayd.
		AFFECT 1667
		ECHO ALL A courier thunders by on his way toward distant Fayd.		
		AFFECT 1653
		ECHO ALL The carpenter sits making dowels.
		AFFECT 1662
		IFVAR DAY = 1
    			ECHO ALL Far out to sea you see 2 good sized sails.
  		ELSE
    			ECHO ALL A cool breeze ruffles your hair. 
  		ENDIF 
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR HOUNDSTEETH = 4
		AFFECT 1641
		ECHO ALL A couple of sentries exchange a joke on the ramparts above you.
		AFFECT 1642
		ECHO ALL A guardsman sits peeling potatoes mumbling about the Black Sands.
		AFFECT 1652
		ECHO ALL A couple of sentries exchange a joke on the ramparts above you.
		AFFECT 1656
		ECHO ALL A guardsman sits peeling potatoes mumbling about his hangover.
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR HOUNDSTEETH = 5
		AFFECT 1641
		ECHO ALL The smell of the desert blows in from the west.
		AFFECT 1642
		ECHO ALL The smell of the desert blows in with a swirl of dust through the narrow arrow slits in the walls.
 	ENDIF
;---------------Highridge Village-------------
	RANDOM HRPLAZA 1 7 0
 	IFVAR HRPLAZA = 1
		AFFECT 1623
		ECHO ALL A few children stop their play to watch you for a moment.
		AFFECT 1622
		ECHO ALL A home owner caulks his door.
		AFFECT 1624
		ECHO ALL A woman harvests the garden near the house.
		AFFECT 1628
		ECHO ALL A group of farmers are harvesting the grain.
		AFFECT 1625
		ECHO ALL The sounds playing children is heard.
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR HRPLAZA = 2
		AFFECT 1623
		ECHO ALL A rooster crows somewhere nearby.
		AFFECT 1624
		ECHO ALL A home owner stacks firewood by his home.
		AFFECT 1622
		ECHO ALL A woman cuts beans from a vine.
		AFFECT 1628
		ECHO ALL A farmer sharpens his scythe.
		AFFECT 1625
		ECHO ALL The sounds of playing children is heard.
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR HRPLAZA = 3
		AFFECT 1623
		ECHO ALL A very pretty young girl in a heavy coat draws water from the well.
		AFFECT 1622
		ECHO ALL A home owner repairs her garden fence.
		AFFECT 1629
		ECHO ALL The sounds of children laughing is heard.
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR HRPLAZA = 4
		AFFECT 1623
		ECHO ALL A group of farmers sit in the shade laughing about something.
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR HRPLAZA = 5
		AFFECT 1623
		ECHO ALL A mother cat herds her kittens across the busy square.
	ENDIF
 	IFVAR HRPLAZA = 6
		AFFECT 1623
		ECHO ALL A pig grunts somewhere nearby.
	ENDIF
;-----------------------------------------
;reset across minute timer
;
	EQUAL ACROSSMIN 0
ENDIF

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             
